High Court’s Corruption and Economic Crimes Division in Dar es Salaam has ruled that Chama cha Demokrasia na Maendeleo (CHADEMA) Chairman, Freeman Mbowe and other three co-accused with a case to answer. Delivering the verdict on Friday, Judge Joachim Tiganga said after reviewing the evidence of 13 state witnesses found all three accused with a case to answer. Mr Mbowe and his colleagues namely; Khalfani Bwire, Adam Kasekwa and Mohammed Ling'wenya are being charged with five crimes including terrorism conspiracy, financing conspiracy and participating in meetings that intend to blow up gas stations.